<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100803778948418></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100803778948418><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=100803778948418>RE: Flash of Light</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=100803778948418#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2076><span id=Sage>Pusbag the Malevolent</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>1244 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Dec 10th 9:29 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>By the way, FoL is a *great* PvP spell.  Cast this one first, then blast 'em back into the Stone Age with your DoTs and DDs.  Remember, all your DoT's stack so you can use this spell order:<br><br>SoW yourself<br>FoL (blind them)<br>Sickness (stops regeneration)<br>all your other DoTs<br>FoL (when your mana gets low)<br>--go hide and med--<br>FoL again<br>Sickness if worn off<br>all your other DoTs.<br>FoL<br>repeat until they are dead.<br><br>A couple of tricks to use:<br>1) Stand ankledeep in water.  Spells do not have an effect of you although they appear to do so to the caster.<br>2) If you can levitate, coax the melee type to the edge of water where you are floating.  Zap him, then move out over the H2O and get him mad by DDing him.  Watch him swim out to you, then kill him in the water.<br>3)  Remember to always FoL your prey.  Blindness gives you a 5-20 second advantage.<br>4)  If you have the deplete strength spell cast it on a WAR and he won't be able to move.<br><br>That's enough to keep you busy for a while.<br><br>--Pusbag Infection<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Dec 10 21:31:07 2001</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
